    name='search',
    response={
      'result': """CVE-2025-31324 is a critical missing authentication vulnerability affecting the Visual Composer component of SAP NetWeaver Application Server Java. This flaw, rated with the highest possible CVSS score of 10.0, allows unauthenticated attackers to upload arbitrary files to the affected system, leading to remote code execution (RCE) and a complete takeover of SAP systems and business data.

The vulnerability primarily impacts SAP NetWeaver versions 7.x, specifically `VCFRAMEWORK 7.50`, and involves sending malicious POST requests to the `/developmentserver/metadatauploader` endpoint.

CVE-2025-31324 has been actively exploited in the wild as a zero-day by sophisticated threat actors, including China-nexus nation-state advanced persistent threat (APT) groups. On August 15, 2025, a public exploit for this vulnerability was released by "Scattered LAPSUS$ Hunters – ShinyHunters" on Telegram.

This vulnerability is often chained with CVE-2025-42999, a deserialization vulnerability in SAP NetWeaver, to escalate privileges and execute code with SAP administrator permissions, providing full access to SAP data and system resources. This combined exploit allows attackers to deploy webshells, execute operating system commands, and maintain persistent access while reducing artifacts on the target system.

SAP released an emergency update (Security Note 3594142) for CVE-2025-31324 on April 24, 2025. A subsequent security advisory on May 13, 2025, addressed CVE-2025-42999 (Security Note 3604119) to remove residual risks. Early workarounds for CVE-2025-31324 were available as of April 8, 2025.

To mitigate the risk, organizations should update SAP NetWeaver to a non-vulnerable version, specifically installing support packages SP027-SP033 for versions 7.50 and above. Additionally, it is recommended to restrict access to the `/developmentserver/metadatauploader` endpoint using firewall policies or SAP Web Dispatcher, and to conduct in-depth investigations for indicators of compromise (IoCs) and unexpected JSP files in relevant SAP server directories. Both CVE-2025-31324 and CVE-2025-42999 were added to CISA's Known Exploited Vulnerabilities (KEV) Catalog on May 15, 2025, underscoring the urgency of patching."""
    }
  )
)] role='user'
